cluster_relations.rel_desc: The butterfly life cycle consists of distinct developmental stages.
cluster_relations.object_entity_name: stages of the butterfly's life cycle

cluster_relations.rel_desc: The newly emerged butterfly is in the adult butterfly life stage, which is the fourth and final stage.

qualifiers.TemporalQualifier: immediately after emergence into the adult stage

remarks: Stage membership inferred from juxtaposition and life-cycle description, not stated in a single explicit clause.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that a life cycle process is composed of specific developmental stages.
args.justification: The subject is the butterfly life cycle as a process and the object is the collection of its stages; the semantics are that the process is composed of these stages.
This relation expresses how a biological process (life cycle) decomposes into constituent stages, fitting a process-vs-stage structural class.
The relation describes a whole (life cycle) being composed of parts (stages), which is a compositional structure.

args.canonical_rel_desc: Indicates that the subject is a concrete instance of the object class or stage type.
args.justification: The newly emerged butterfly is a specific individual that belongs to the adult butterfly life stage category; this is standard instance–class semantics.
The link classifies an individual entity as belonging to a particular life stage type, which is an instance–class classification relation.
Instance-of expresses what kind of thing the subject is; this is an identity/classification dimension rather than causal or temporal.
